Veteran Rapper and talk show host, Ruggedman has announced that he would be featuring pop stars, Falz, Small Doctor, and producer, Masterkraft in a new single. The musician, whose real name is Michael Ugochukwu Stephens posted an interview he had with entertainment platform, Hiptv, on his Instagram, on Tuesday. The rapper who has been out of music circulation also posted on his verified social media platform, “A lot of people have asked me for new music. It’s almost time @falzthebahdguy @iam_smalldoctor @masterkraft_” “I already have a new song coming out soon, Masterkraft is already working on it. Ruggedman featuring Falz D Bad Guy, and Small Doctor. It has been a while, although I dropped a conscious EP in 2021…wait for the new music and wait for the new show,” he said in the video clip. Ruggedy Baba came into the limelight with fresh punchlines in his epochal diss track, “Ehen” featuring the late Nomoreloss. The rapper took on the creme of the Nigerian music scene at the time, Eedris Abdulkareem, Olu Maintain, and others in the single at the time. The “Baraje” rapper later earned his veteran status with four rap albums among which are Thy Album Come, and Ruggedy Baba, among others. In recent times, Ruggedman had played its part in activism, especially at the EndSars protest. It was earlier reported he blasted the Federal Government when it placed on ban on Twitter recently. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com